The article is a statement by NSC Deputy Spokesman Ben Chang on a meeting that took place between National Security Advisor Tom Donilon, Foreign Minister Seiji Maehara of Japan, and Foreign Minister Kim Sung-hwan of the Republic of Korea. The meeting was part of the historic Trilateral meetings between the three countries. Donilon expressed the President's support and personal interest in the Trilateral process, emphasizing its timeliness in response to recent North Korean provocations. The officials pledged to remain coordinated in sending a clear message to North Korea regarding denuclearization. They also discussed ways to enhance collaboration and cooperation on regional and global issues.